Quick question I've been noodling on. Several of our portfolio companies are exploring on-device AI agents for their employees. The privacy story is compelling, but I keep coming back to governance: if we deploy agents on employee devices that can read files and execute commands, how do we ensure they operate within defined data boundaries? What does the audit trail look like? Is there a permission model that IT can enforce?

I'd love to chat about this tonight if you have a moment. No need for a formal presentation — just your perspective on where the guardrails are today and where they're heading.

